The paper focuses on the automated testing of certificate verification in SSL/TLS implementations using deep reinforcement learning. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since deep reinforcement learning is used. The paper also involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it proposes a new framework for automated testing. Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as feature extraction and differential testing, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY), respectively.
